# Feature: Stripe Subscription Integration

## /speckit.specify

### Feature Overview
Implement a comprehensive subscription system using Stripe, supporting Free, Monthly Premium, and Yearly Premium tiers. The system includes checkout flows, webhook handling, subscription management, and discount code application.

### Feature Scope
- **Subscription Tiers:** Free (default), Monthly Premium ($9.99), Yearly Premium ($99).
- **Stripe Integration:** Checkout sessions, customer portal, webhook processing.
- **Discount System:** Apply reward codes to subscriptions.
- **User Management:** View status, cancel, reactivate, update payment methods.
- **Access Control:** Gate content based on subscription status.

### User Stories
1. As a **Free User**, I want to see a comparison of plans so I can decide to upgrade.
2. As a **User**, I want to subscribe to a Premium plan using a secure checkout.
3. As a **User**, I want to apply a discount code from my rewards to get a lower price.
4. As a **Subscriber**, I want to view my billing history and download invoices.
5. As a **Subscriber**, I want to cancel my subscription but keep access until the period ends.
6. As an **Admin**, I want the system to automatically handle failed payments and expirations.
7. As a **User**, I want to update my credit card information easily.

### Technical Requirements
- **Stripe SDK:** Use official Stripe libraries for .NET and React.
- **Webhooks:** Secure endpoint to handle `checkout.session.completed`, `invoice.paid`, `customer.subscription.deleted`, etc.
- **Database:** Store Stripe Customer ID, Subscription ID, Status, and Period End.
- **Security:** Verify webhook signatures, never expose secret keys, HTTPS only.
- **State Sync:** Ensure local database reflects Stripe status accurately (eventual consistency via webhooks).

