## /speckit.clarify

### Questions & Answers

**Q: How do we handle plan upgrades/downgrades?**
A: Stripe Checkout handles upgrades/downgrades. We will direct users to the Customer Portal or a new Checkout Session for plan changes. Proration will be handled by Stripe default settings.

**Q: What happens if a payment fails?**
A: Stripe retries according to settings (Smart Retries). We listen for `invoice.payment_failed`. After 3 days (grace period), if unpaid, the webhook `customer.subscription.deleted` or `updated` will trigger a downgrade to Free locally.

**Q: Can users use multiple discount codes?**
A: No, only one discount code per subscription. The system must validate the code against the user's earned rewards and mark it as 'used' upon successful payment event.

**Q: Do we store credit card details?**
A: **NEVER**. We only store the Stripe Customer ID. All sensitive data is handled by Stripe.

**Q: How do we sync local dev with Stripe webhooks?**
A: Use the Stripe CLI (`stripe listen --forward-to localhost:5000/api/webhooks`) for local development.

